On Dec 17, 2005, at 3:29 PM, Mark Hineline wrote:

> 1. Take the tank out.
> 2. Put a length of chain into an otherwise dry tank and shake it
> 3. Hose out with water. Repeat until no more gunk and varnish come  
> out.
> 4. Treat the inside with dilute acid (muriatic). Neutralize, then  
> rinse out.
> 5. Treat with POR 15 tank sealer.

To get the sludge out I had to use Marine Clean from the POR-15 auto  
tank resto kit:

http://www.ratwell.com/technical/FuelTankRestoration.html

It' dissolved it all.

